defaulton
default the impact of the Scottish rate of income tax on aspects of the UK income tax system including income tax reliefs.  The consultation 
defaultcontributed to 
defaultthe approach to the treatment of reliefs for Scottish taxpayers in 
defaultHMRC’s Technical Note, published 
defaultin 
defaultMay 2012
default.
default 
default&#xa0;
defaultBefore making any orders under this section, to amend 
defaultthe application of the Welsh rate of 
defaultincome tax
default to tax reliefs
default,
default 
defaultthe 
defaultUK Government would consult relevant stakeholders. 
defaultOur starting point would be the results of the previous consultation, so we would expect that 
defaultthe approach taken in these areas, including the treatment of tax relief for charitable donations and pension contributions would follow the proposals in the
default 
defaultTechnical Note
default, 
defaultsubject to
default any changes in the tax system or 
defaultin the capability of IT systems in the interim.
default 
