defaultThe devolution of income tax reliefs is not within scope of this Bill. 
defaultThe Welsh Government’s power relates only to the rate of income tax – we would expect the Welsh Government to be involved in 
defaultconsultation
default in relation to reliefs, but the final decision would rest with the UK Government because of the potential for wider impacts on the income tax system as a whole.
